    "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nHello,\n\nThe package [metrohash](https://github.com/escherba/python-metrohash) can no longer be built from source \"out of the box\", because it fails when built using Cython 3.1.0.\n\nI've raised escherba/python-metrohash#29 to that project's maintainers about this issue, but I am also wondering if it is a bug in Cython - I can't see a relevant deprecation relating to \"long\" in the 3.1.0 changelogs.\n\nShould the following code work, or is this a regression in Cython?\n\n```\n      Error compiling Cython file:\n      ------------------------------------------------------------\n      ...\n              PyObject_GetBuffer(data, &buf, PyBUF_SIMPLE)\n              result = c_metrohash128(<const uint8 *>buf.buf, buf.len, seed)\n              PyBuffer_Release(&buf)\n          else:\n              raise _type_error(\"data\", [\"basestring\", \"buffer\"], data)\n          return (long(result.first) << 64ULL) + long(result.second)\n                  ^\n      ------------------------------------------------------------\n\n      src/metrohash.pyx:253:12: 'long' is not a constant, variable or function identifier\n```\n\nThanks,\nTom\n\n### Code to reproduce the behaviour:\n\n```cython\n        cdef uint8 buf[16]\n        self._m.Finalize(buf)\n        cdef uint128 result = c_bytes2int128(buf)\n        return (long(result.first) << 64ULL) + long(result.second)\n```\nhttps://github.com/escherba/python-metrohash/blob/0.3.2/src/metrohash.pyx#L467-L470\n\n### Expected behaviour\n\nCompilation successful\n\n### OS\n\nLinux\n\n### Python version\n\n3.12\n\n### Cython version\n\n3.1.0\n\n### Additional context\n\nMetrohash might well have become unmaintained at this point, it hasn't been changed in a while... But either way, I would like to know if this behaviour is expected, or a genuine bug in Cython please!",
